cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with object annotation in images using speech and mouse inputs. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) domains. Additionally, the paper discusses the advantages of using speech-based interfaces, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The experiments involve working with large datasets, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
